1
00:01:35,264 --> 00:01:38,912
 

2
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:47,840
Li Jun.

3
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:56,079
Do you think Si Si's boyfriend knows she's lying?

4
00:01:56,079 --> 00:01:59,560
Whether he knows or not isn't important.

5
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:02,640
What matters is that he now
understands Si Si's stance,

6
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:04,860
so he probably won't come looking for her.

7
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:09,199
That sounds so sad.

8
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:13,900
Really? I actually feel relieved for them.

9
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:18,159
They've been entangled
like this for almost a year.

10
00:02:18,159 --> 00:02:20,120
Today, they finally cleared the air.

11
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:23,060
It's a kind of liberation for both of them.

12
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:26,260
I thought you two were close friends.

13
00:02:26,939 --> 00:02:28,999
We are close friends.

14
00:02:29,819 --> 00:02:32,919
This has nothing to do
with being good friends or not.

15
00:02:32,919 --> 00:02:35,979
Take what happened
outside the dorm tonight for example.

16
00:02:35,979 --> 00:02:38,939
Those couples looked so deeply in love.

17
00:02:38,939 --> 00:02:40,900
But check back in a few months,

18
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:42,840
they will be hugging

19
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:45,020
and kissing a different person.

20
00:02:45,020 --> 00:02:47,379
No one remembers anyone for long.

21
00:02:47,379 --> 00:02:49,060
We're about to graduate.

22
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:53,300
Everyone will go their separate ways
for various reasons.

23
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:57,500
That's not necessarily true.

24
00:02:57,500 --> 00:03:00,080
Some people do stay together for a long time.

25
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:04,280
Who? Give me one example.

26
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:06,599
- Well, like my...
- Don't mention your parents.

27
00:03:06,599 --> 00:03:08,880
You know that's different.

28
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:16,620
Li Jun, you're only three years older than me.

29
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:19,659
Why do you always act like an adult around me?

30
00:03:19,659 --> 00:03:21,360
What do you mean by "act"?

31
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,780
I am an adult!

32
00:03:23,780 --> 00:03:26,039
You'll become an adult after 18.

33
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:28,419
Welcome to the adult world.

34
00:03:28,419 --> 00:03:31,380
It's realistic and cruel here.

35
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:40,779
Can't adults have people they like?

36
00:03:42,159 --> 00:03:44,099
Did you say anything?

37
00:03:44,099 --> 00:03:48,659
I mean, adults can have people they like.

38
00:03:48,659 --> 00:03:51,259
What about you? Do you have someone you like?

39
00:03:51,259 --> 00:03:53,039
Of course I do.

40
00:03:53,039 --> 00:03:55,059
See?

41
00:03:56,919 --> 00:04:00,019
So what kind of person are they?

42
00:04:04,919 --> 00:04:08,300
We've known each other since childhood.

43
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:11,219
He's different from everyone else I know.

44
00:04:11,219 --> 00:04:15,519
He never understands what I say
and does things far from my world.

45
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:21,019
But he's incredibly beautiful.

46
00:04:21,019 --> 00:04:26,800
Time seems to stop when I see him,

47
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,860
and butterflies fill my stomach.

48
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:31,840
Me too.

49
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:36,739
I've also known the person I like since childhood.

50
00:04:37,740 --> 00:04:42,360
And sometimes,
I also feel those things you described.

51
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:46,740
But the person I like is 15 years older than me.

52
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:49,800
About eight years ago, he got married.

53
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:52,079
His wife is also stunningly beautiful.

54
00:04:52,079 --> 00:04:54,600
They look perfect together.

55
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:58,560
Seeing how well-matched they are,
I can't even be upset.

56
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,319
They even have two kids now.

57
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:02,540
Wait, hold on a second.

58
00:05:02,540 --> 00:05:05,980
The person you like is married with children?

59
00:05:05,980 --> 00:05:08,360
He got married eight years ago!

60
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:10,379
But you were only 13 back then!

61
00:05:13,259 --> 00:05:17,699
The person I like is a celebrity!

62
00:05:20,959 --> 00:05:24,959
Why? I really like him!

63
00:05:24,959 --> 00:05:27,000
What about you, Cherry?

64
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,800
I'm not telling you.

65
00:05:29,839 --> 00:05:32,220
Liar! You're so mean.

66
00:05:33,399 --> 00:05:35,439
Liar.

67
00:05:35,439 --> 00:05:37,439
You... liar!

68
00:05:45,939 --> 00:05:49,620
 Jiang Qiao Xi, I just found out today 

69
00:05:49,620 --> 00:05:55,860
 that the adult world after 18 isn't fun at all. 

70
00:05:56,540 --> 00:05:59,379
 Did you enter that adult world first 

71
00:05:59,379 --> 00:06:01,600
 and that's why I can't find you? 

72
